# Circle skills first (save debugging time)

When changing or fixing anything involving **Circle products**, **do not** rely only on trial-and-error. **Read the relevant `SKILL.md` under `.agents/skills/`** (and its `references/` if needed) **before** deep debugging.

## Skill index → use when

| Skill folder | Use for |
|--------------|---------|
| `bridge-stablecoin` | Bridge Kit, CCTP, cross-chain USDC |
| `use-arc` | Arc chain, USDC gas, Arc contracts |
| `use-circle-wallets` | Choosing wallet type (DCW vs user vs modular) |
| `use-developer-controlled-wallets` | DCW, wallet sets, entity secret, transfers |
| `use-gateway` | Gateway unified balance, gatewayMint, deposits |
| `use-modular-wallets` | Passkey / MSCA, Gas Station, user operations |
| `use-smart-contract-platform` | Circle SCP deploy, ABI calls, templates |
| `use-usdc` | USDC balances, transfers, allowances (EVM / Solana) |
| `use-user-controlled-wallets` | Social/email OTP embedded wallets, MPC |

Also check **`lib/circleWallet.ts`**, **`lib/dcw.ts`**, **`lib/arc-config.ts`**, and **`api/wallet.ts`** for how this repo wires Circle.

The Circle plugin is enabled in `.cursor/settings.json`; repo skills in `.agents/skills/` are the local source of truth for workflows.
